section.section:
If the secretary of transportation determines, upon the basis of an engineering and traffic investigation, that any speed limit is greater or less than is reasonable or safe under the conditions found to exist at any intersection, or upon any part of a state highway, the secretary of transportation may establish by official order a reasonable and safe speed limit at the location. The secretary shall not increase any speed limit established by subsection (3) of this section in excess of sixty-five (65) miles per hour, except that, notwithstanding the provisions of subsection (3)(a) of this section, the secretary may increase the speed limit on any of the following segments of highway to seventy (70) miles per hour:
Interstate 24 (entire length);
Interstate 64 from Interstate 264 to the West Virginia state line;
Interstate 65 from Interstate 264 to the Tennessee state line;
Interstate 69 (entire length);
Interstate 71 from Interstate 264 to Interstate 275;
Interstate 75 from the Tennessee state line to Interstate 275;
The Audubon Parkway (entire length);
The Julian M. Carroll Purchase Parkway (entire length);
The Bert T. Combs Mountain Parkway from Interstate 64 to the beginning of the Mountain Parkway Extension (KY 9009) in Wolfe County;
The Edward T. Breathitt Pennyrile Parkway (entire length);
The Wendell H. Ford Western Kentucky Parkway (entire length);
The Louie B. Nunn Cumberland Parkway (entire length);
The Martha Layne Collins Bluegrass Parkway (entire length); and
The William H. Natcher Parkway (entire length).
